natspec.details: This contracts imports and provides functions       that deploys each imported contract.

deploySoulbound(string,string).details: Deploys the Soulbound Contract with a set name       and symbol.

deploySoulboundCore(string,string,addres.details: Deploys the SoulboundCore Contract with its constructor       parameters.

params._allowlistOwner: Desired owner of the contrat for sigs.

isPaused().details: Returns true or false if the contract is paused.        This function is callable by anyone.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Pauses the contract.        This function is callable by the owner or deployer.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unPause().details: Pauses the contract.        This function is callable by the owner or deployer.
